cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on solving the problem of dense image matching, which is a core topic in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel optimization algorithm that can be massively parallelized, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of energy minimization and non-convex regularizers, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper demonstrates its real-time performance for the applications of dense stereo matching and optical flow, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
